title: McLennan County Administrator Dustin Chapman Josh Tetens/DA's Office Special Prosecutor Inquiries

communications.subject: Texas Public Information Act Request: McLennan County Administrator Dustin Chapman Josh Tetens/DA's Office Special Prosecutor Inquiries
communications.communication:
To Whom It May Concern:

Pursuant to the Texas Public Information Act, I hereby request the following records:

Names of individuals, names of State Entities, example Attorney General's Office, who have been contacted by the McLennan County DA's office via phone calls, emails, written letters, messages of any kind, in regards to Complaints filed by Citizens in McLennan County. Mr. Tetens has written me telling me that there are numerous people and entities he or someone in his office has contacted and that all of them have refused to take any of the Complaints. Please send me the names of who he is referring to. The email from Mr. Tetens to me is enclosed.     


 
From:
josh.tetens@co.mclennan.tx.us
To:
bfeazell@yahoo.com

Thu, May 1 at 10:59 AM

Dear Ms. Feazell,

 

The Rangers still have those cases, but our office has yet to find another office willing to accept the cases for further review and/or prosecution. Weekly we reach out to new offices requesting they accept the cases, but all, including the Attorney General’s Office, have refused to date.

 

Thank you,
Josh Tetens


Please also know that when Sterling, the lawyer who will get this, does get this he will, once again try to buy time and ask me to prove that this is indeed Bernadette Feazell, so please, once again enlighten him to google "muckrock" and see that, indeed, other places honor Muckrock and perhaps he should read about it and honor it also.  Muckrock is a Public Information non profit, and easily found by a search.

The requested documents will be made available to the general public, and this request is not being made for commercial purposes.

In the event that there are fees, I would be grateful if you would inform me of the total charges in advance of fulfilling my request. I would prefer the request filled electronically, by e-mail attachment if available or CD-ROM if not.

Thank you in advance for your anticipated cooperation in this matter. I look forward to receiving your response to this request within 10 business days, as the statute requires.

Sincerely,

Bernadette Feazell

title: Freedom of Information Act (FOIA) Request: Body-Worn Camera Footage - Arrest of Matthew Leibach (February  14, 2023)

communications.subject: The Missouri Sunshine Law Request: Freedom of Information Act (FOIA) Request: Body-Worn Camera Footage - Arrest of Matthew Leibach (February  14, 2023)
communications.communication:
To Whom It May Concern:

Pursuant to the The Missouri Sunshine Law, I hereby request the following records:

Pursuant to Chapter 610 of the Missouri Revised Statutes, also known as the Missouri Sunshine Law, primarily deals with the public's right to access information from public governmental bodies in Missouri.

I respectfully request copies of all body-worn camera (BWC) footage related to the arrest of Matthew Leibach on or about February  14, 2023 at approximately 4:48 AM, by the St. Louis County Police.

Specifically, I am requesting:
All body-worn camera footage recorded by any St. Louis County Police Department personnel during the detention, investigation, or arrest of Matthew Leibach also footage of the vehicle chase that resulted in Matthew Leibach crashing the vehicle at Ohio Avenue and Broadway Street in St. Louis City.

Please include footage captured shortly before, during, and immediately after the incident

The requested documents will be made available to the general public, and this request is not being made for commercial purposes.

In the event that there are fees, I would be grateful if you would inform me of the total charges in advance of fulfilling my request. I would prefer the request filled electronically, by e-mail attachment if available or CD-ROM if not.

Thank you in advance for your anticipated cooperation in this matter. I look forward to receiving your response to this request within 3 business days, as the statute requires.

Sincerely,

Brandon Martin
